#    - Automatic HTTPS
#    - Global CDN
#    - Free tier available
#    - https://vercel.com
#
# 2. Netlify
#    - Similar to Vercel
#    - Great for static sites
#    - Free tier available
#    - https://netlify.com
#
# 3. Cloudflare Pages
#    - Fast global CDN
#    - Generous free tier
#    - https://pages.cloudflare.com
#
# 4. AWS Amplify
#    - Full AWS integration
#    - More complex setup
#    - https://aws.amazon.com/amplify/
#
# ============ ENVIRONMENT VARIABLE INJECTION ============
#
# Most hosting platforms allow you to set environment variables in their dashboard:
#
# Vercel:
# 1. Go to Project Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Add each REACT_APP_* variable
# 3. Set for "Production" environment
# 4. Redeploy
#
# Netlify:
# 1. Go to Site Settings → Environment Variables
# 2. Add each REACT_APP_* variable
# 3. Redeploy
#
# This is MORE SECURE than committing .env.production with real keys!
#
# ============ IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES ============
#
# 1. NEVER commit Stripe SECRET keys (sk_*)
#    ✅ Publishable keys (pk_*) are safe to commit
#    ❌ Secret keys (sk_*) must NEVER be in frontend
#
# 2. Source maps
#    GENERATE_SOURCEMAP=false prevents exposing your source code
#
# 3. API keys in frontend
#    Remember: ALL REACT_APP_* variables are PUBLIC
#    They're embedded in the JavaScript bundle
#    Users can see them in browser DevTools
#    Only put PUBLISHABLE keys here (never secrets)
#
# 4. Backend security
#    All sensitive operations must be on backend
#    Frontend just calls API endpoints
#    Backend validates everything
#
# ========================================
